  "text": "All assays were performed at 25uC essentially as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, EPEC was cultured in Luria-Bertani (LB) broth overnight to an OD 600 of 0.8-1.0 and 170 mL spread on 6 cm LB agar (Fisher) plates containing 2 mg/mL tryptophan (LBT plates). After incubation for 20 hours at 37uC, the LBT/ EPEC plates were cooled in 25uC incubators for an hour. Young adult worms, maintained at 20uC, were collected with M9 buffer (3 g KH 2 PO 4 , 6 g Na 2 HPO 4 , 5 g NaCl, 1 mL 1 M MgSO 4 in 1 L of water) and exposed to EPEC for 3 hours at 25uC before being transferred to OP50 on NGM plates. After 24 hours at room temperature, worms were gently prodded with a platinum wire and considered dead if they failed to respond to touch and showed no indication of pharyngeal pumping. At least 250 worms were tested for each experiment.",
